WEBVTT

00:00:03.300 --> 00:00:04.860
NARRATOR: We are inseparable.

00:00:04.860 --> 00:00:05.830
We're best friends.

00:00:05.830 --> 00:00:07.530
MAN: Anywhere you find humans

00:00:07.530 --> 00:00:08.700
you will almost
certainly find dogs.

00:00:08.700 --> 00:00:13.060
NARRATOR: And they are smarter
than we ever imagined.

00:00:13.060 --> 00:00:16.100
Astonishing new
research is revealing

00:00:16.100 --> 00:00:18.800
that dogs are far more than
merely tamed wild animals.

00:00:18.800 --> 00:00:21.700
MAN: What makes our
relationships so special
is the dog's ability

00:00:21.700 --> 00:00:24.460
to be able to read our
emotions so effectively.

00:00:24.460 --> 00:00:27.430
NARRATOR: Have they evolved
a new kind of intelligence?

00:00:27.430 --> 00:00:28.630
WOMAN: Suddenly
there were dogs doing

00:00:28.630 --> 00:00:33.800
something that not
even chimps could do.

00:00:33.800 --> 00:00:38.100
NARRATOR: Have
dogs developed a language to
communicate complex emotions?

00:00:38.100 --> 00:00:40.430
MAN: Anger, fear,
happiness, despair.

00:00:40.430 --> 00:00:47.830
MAN: You can almost understand
what they're thinking.

00:00:47.830 --> 00:00:51.800
NARRATOR: Why do we love
an animal that was once
a fearsome predator?

00:00:51.800 --> 00:00:55.430
How did dogs go from this...

00:00:55.430 --> 00:00:57.160
to this?

00:00:57.160 --> 00:01:02.260
Is it in the genes or
the way we treat them?

00:01:02.260 --> 00:01:05.630
And when did it all begin?

00:01:05.630 --> 00:01:06.930
The bones tell one story...

00:01:06.930 --> 00:01:10.400
We start seeing the
first things 1 2,000
or 13,000 years ago.

00:01:10.400 --> 00:01:11.930
NARRATOR: The
genes tell another.

00:01:11.930 --> 00:01:14.130
100,000 years or more.

00:01:14.130 --> 00:01:18.700
NARRATOR: The answer is more
important than you might think.

00:01:18.700 --> 00:01:21.130
MAN: Without dog
domestication,

00:01:21.130 --> 00:01:23.200
civilization just would
not have been possible.

00:01:23.200 --> 00:01:41.130
NARRATOR: ''Dogs Decoded,''
right now on NoVA.

